  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency response to upgrade the inadequate shelters of vulnerable families in Hebron&#x2019;s H2 area to protect them from attacks by Israeli military and settlers, as well as from natural hazards.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will target the most vulnerable families in Hebron city&#x2019;s H2 area i.e. those living in inadequate shelters close to Israeli settlements and military points. These families face a challenging environment which includes restrictions on movement and shelter rehabilitation, settler violence and military attacks these factors strongly expose them to the risk of forced displacement.
The proposed shelter renovation includes the supply and installation of protection elements (fences, gates, steel window nets, yard and alley covers) as well as renovation inputs (treat dampness, improve WASH connections and facilities, treat leaky roofs and walls, replace doors and windows)
Thus, the proposed action will strengthen the target beneficiaries&#x2019; resilience by (1) protecting them from harsh weather conditions, particularly during the winter when they are exposed to ceiling leaks and wind (2) mitigate the risks associated with Israeli military and settler violence in particular during clashes and (3) generally improve their living standards by rehabilitating their structurally unsound and inadequate shelters.</narrative>
  </description>
